sequenceDiagram
    autonumber

    participant Client as External Client
    participant Router as OpenShift Router<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant KRBP as kube-rbac-proxy Sidecar<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API Server<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS
    participant REST as REST Container<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    participant DB as PostgreSQL / MySQL<br/>5432/3306 TCP

    rect rgb(230, 245, 255)
        Note over Client,DB: Flow 1: Model Registry REST API Request (External)
        Client->>Router: POST /v1/model_registry/{id}/...<br/>HTTPS TLS (edge)
        Router->>KRBP: Forward request<br/>HTTPS TLS (reencrypt)
        KRBP->>K8sAPI: TokenReview<br/>HTTPS TLS, SA token
        K8sAPI-->>KRBP: Token valid
        KRBP->>K8sAPI: SubjectAccessReview<br/>(services/get on registry Service)
        K8sAPI-->>KRBP: Authorized
        KRBP->>REST: Forward (pre-authorized)<br/>HTTP localhost:8080
        REST->>DB: Query/Write metadata<br/>DB protocol, configurable SSL<br/>username/password auth
        DB-->>REST: Result set
        REST-->>KRBP: JSON Response
        KRBP-->>Router: HTTPS Response
        Router-->>Client: HTTPS Response
    end

    participant Operator as Model Registry Operator<br/>controller-runtime
    participant OSConfig as OpenShift Config API

    rect rgb(255, 245, 230)
        Note over K8sAPI,OSConfig: Flow 2: Model Registry Reconciliation
        K8sAPI->>Operator: Watch event (ModelRegistry CR change)<br/>HTTPS TLS, SA token
        Operator->>K8sAPI: Create/Update resources<br/>(Deployment, Service, Route,<br/>NetworkPolicy, RBAC, Secrets)<br/>HTTPS TLS, SA token
        Operator->>OSConfig: Read ingress domain<br/>(config.openshift.io/ingresses)<br/>HTTPS TLS, SA token
        OSConfig-->>Operator: Cluster domain
        Operator->>K8sAPI: Read pod logs<br/>(error detection)<br/>HTTPS TLS, SA token
        K8sAPI-->>Operator: Pod log stream
    end

    participant InitCatalog as Init Containers<br/>(catalog-data + benchmark)
    participant CatalogREST as Catalog Container<br/>8080/TCP
    participant CatalogDB as Catalog PostgreSQL<br/>5432/TCP
    participant ConfigMaps as Catalog Source<br/>ConfigMaps

    rect rgb(245, 255, 230)
        Note over InitCatalog,ConfigMaps: Flow 3: Model Catalog Startup
        InitCatalog->>InitCatalog: Copy catalog data YAML<br/>to emptyDir volume
        InitCatalog->>InitCatalog: Copy benchmark data<br/>to emptyDir volume
        CatalogREST->>CatalogDB: Connect<br/>PostgreSQL plaintext<br/>username/password (Secret)
        CatalogDB-->>CatalogREST: Connection established
        CatalogREST->>ConfigMaps: Read catalog sources<br/>(mounted volumes)
        ConfigMaps-->>CatalogREST: Source definitions
    end
